main event: A bright star-like object was seen rotating in the sky over Seria, Borneo, emitting twin jets of vapor.
interesting points: The object was visible for 40 minutes.
Similar phenomena have been reported over Borneo several times recently.
The object was estimated to be at an altitude of 30,000 feet.
The spectators referred to the object as a 'flying saucer' for want of a better explanation.
The report states that there was 'insufficient data for evaluation' and that the conclusion was 'INSUFFICIENT DATA FOR EVALUATION'.
sighted object: a bright star-like object rotating in the sky and emitting twin jets of vapor
